{"id":"synth-data-1l0.26","title":"Tech stack decision: Python 3.11+ with pinned office-file libraries","description":"Language: Python 3.11+ (spec mandates it in §2.1/§2.2).\n\nPinned stack:\n- openpyxl — xlsx read/write (formulas, merged cells, formatting)\n- python-docx — docx (styles, headers, tables)\n- reportlab — text-native PDFs\n- fpdf2 — scanned-style PDFs (low-res image output)\n- pypdf — PDF read-back for auto-grader\n- pandas + numpy — financial data generation, 52K-row AP ledger, Benford analysis\n- faker — synthetic names/addresses (with fixed seed)\n- pyyaml — config.yaml\n- pytest — generator + grader tests\n- uv (or poetry) — lockfile for reproducibility\n\nDeterminism rules (required by §9 quality gate: byte-identical reruns):\n- random.seed(42) + numpy.random.default_rng(42)\n- Avoid unordered set iteration; sort dict keys before writing\n- Faker: Faker.seed(42) and per-instance seeding\n- Lock all dependency versions via lockfile\n\nPDF DETERMINISM GOTCHA: reportlab embeds timestamps and producer strings by default, which breaks byte-identical reruns. Must set invariant=True on Canvas and pin a fixed creation date in document metadata. fpdf2 has a similar issue — set creation_date and modification_date explicitly. Verify this early by running the generator twice and diffing the PDF outputs; do not wait until the §9 quality gate to discover it.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"chore","owner":"platon2001@icloud.com","created_at":"2026-04-08T13:56:06Z","created_by":"platon2001","updated_at":"2026-04-08T14:05:32Z","closed_at":"2026-04-08T16:05:32Z","close_reason":"Decision recorded. Stack is locked: Python 3.11+, openpyxl/python-docx/reportlab/fpdf2/pypdf/pandas/numpy/faker/pyyaml/pytest/uv. Determinism rules and PDF timestamp gotcha documented in description for reference by dependent beads.","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"synth-data-1l0.26","depends_on_id":"synth-data-1l0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-08T15:56:06Z","created_by":"platon2001","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":5,"comment_count":0}
